TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
$BBOLD Matrices Inverses. $EBOLD Know how to compute matrix inverses and 
use them to solve linear systems.  For example, if
$BR
\[
A = \begin{bmatrix}1 & 2 \\ -1 & 2 \end{bmatrix}
\]
then


$BR
\[
A^{-1} =
\begin{bmatrix}a & b \\ c & d \end{bmatrix}
\]
where
$BR
\(a = \) \{ ans_rule(10) \} ,
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(1/2));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
$BR
\(b = \) \{ ans_rule(10) \} ,
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(-1/2));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
$BR
\(c = \) \{ ans_rule(10) \} ,
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(1/4));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
$BR
\(d = \) \{ ans_rule(10) \} ,
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(1/4));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
$BR
Use it to solve the linear system
\[
\begin{array}{rcl}
x+y &=& 1 \\
-x+2y &=& 2 \\
\end{array}
\]

You obtain
$BR
\(x = \) \{ ans_rule(10) \} ,
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(0));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
$BR
\(y = \) \{ ans_rule(10) \} ,
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(1));




